node.title: Tasmania records new COVID case after man arrives on flight from Brisbane
node.alt: Visitors walk under Hobart Airport sign
node.description: The Victorian man was meant to travel to Melbourne via Hobart without leaving the airport. But after his arrival, Tasmanian authorities were notified by their counterparts in Queensland he had returned a positive test.
node.content: ["A Victorian man who entered Tasmania from Brisbane on Sunday has been confirmed as a positive COVID-19 case.", "The man had intended to travel\u00a0to Melbourne via Hobart this afternoon without leaving the airport but was not allowed to board the flight after Tasmanian Public Health authorities were told by their Queensland counterparts a test conducted on the man had come back positive.\u00a0", "The man was taken directly to the Fountainside quarantine facility in Hobart.", "Passengers on Virgin flight VA702 from Brisbane to Hobart, which arrived around 12:15pm on Sunday, are being asked to isolate immediately and phone the Public Health Hotline.", "People who were in the Hobart Airport Terminal between 12:15 - 2:45pm are also being asked to isolate immediately", "Public health is in the process of contacting people on the flight and those who use the Check-In Tas app when entering the airport."]
